'''Mazel Tov''' ({{lang-he|מזל טוב}}) means "good luck/fortune" in [[Hebrew language|Hebrew]] and incorporated into [[Yiddish language|Yiddish]], and is now used in English as well. It is often used in place of "congratulations."  

The expression may possibly come from the [[Akkadian language]] ''manzaltu, mazzaztum,'' "position of a star," from ''izuzzu,'' "to stand." This descended to the [[Mishnaic Hebrew]] ''mazzāl'', meaning "[[constellation]]" or "[[destiny]]." Adding the word tôb, meaning "good," a direct English translation would be "good destiny" or "good [[fortune]]." [http://www.answers.com/mazel+tov&r=67]

Like other [[blessings]] it is often said frequently and sometimes loudly at [[Jewish]] celebrations.  It is commonly used within the Jewish community.  In colloquial language, "Mazel tov" is sometimes said sarcastically when congratulations are not appropriate or due.

"Mazel Tov" Is also a modern grunge band formed for Endrigo Miceli, Mike Dukart, Caio Coimbra, Jeff Tauchen and Rodrigo Mazer.

